The Defend our Democracy campaign is mobilising South Africans to protect the Constitution. JOHANNESBURG - The year 1994 brought promise and heightened expectations but some of that hope has been bashed by those entrusted with building the county. That's according to the Defend Our Democracy programme - endorsed by ANC veterans such and the Desmond and Leah Foundation. READ: SACP: Zuma holding SA's democracy to ransom They're calling for South Africans to protect the Constitution, especially in light of former President Jacob Zuma's refusal to appear before the Zondo Commission. The organisation formed a human chain outside the Constitutional Court in Johannesburg on Monday evening. eNCA's Masego Rahlaga shares more details in the video above.